    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Organisms able to live and reproduce only in the presence of free oxygen; having an oxygen-based metabolism in which they utilize cellular respiration to use oxygen to oxidize substrates (for example sugars and fats) in order to obtain energy. Obligate or strict aerobes can live only in the presence of oxygen; facultative aerobes are capable of living in its absence as well as in its presence. Used especially in reference to microorganisms.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>只能在有氧環境中生存與繁殖的有機體；它們以氧氣為基礎進行新陳代謝，利用細胞的呼吸作用，藉由氧氣來氧化基質(例如糖與脂肪)，以獲得能量。專性好氧生物只能在有氧環境中生存；兼性好氧生物能在有氧與無氧環境中生存。此詞彙特別用於指微生物。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Organismen die alleen kunnen leven en zich voortplanten in aanwezigheid van zuurstof. Ze hebben een op zuurstof gebaseerde stofwisseling, waarbij ze door cellulaire ademhaling zuurstof gebruiken om substraten (bijvoorbeeld suikers en vetten) te oxideren en zo energie te verkrijgen. Obligaat of strikt aerobe organismen kunnen alleen leven in de aanwezigheid van zuurstof; facultatief aerobe organismen kunnen zowel met als zonder zuurstof leven. Vooral gebruikt met betrekking tot micro-organismen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
